This is Perl module optimizer::hotspot.

INSTALLATION

optimizer::hotspot installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    $ cpan optimizer::hotspot

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

optimizer::hotspot documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc optimizer::hotspot

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

